<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>13 SPEED AND 18 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO-713/18 SERIES - REMOVE - OUTPUT YOKE/COMPANION FLANGE
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="3">
        <title>OUTPUT YOKE/COMPANION FLANGE</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>The shifter housing must be removed to lock the transmission.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>After removal of the output yoke/companion flange, temporarily replace the output shaft nut to
                    protect the output shaft threads during auxiliary section disassembly.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Engage two (2) mainshaft sliding clutches into two (2) mainshaft gears to lock the
                transmission (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300718">Figure 18</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300718" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300718" filename="../figg13/G1300718.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 18. Engage Mainshaft Sliding Clutches</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a large breaker bar or air impact wrench to remove the output shaft nut (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300719">Figure 19</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300719" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300719" filename="../figg13/G1300719.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 19. Remove Output Shaft Nut</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Pull the yoke or flange straight to the rear and off the output shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300720">Figure 20</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300720" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300720" filename="../figg13/G1300720.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 20. Pull Yoke or Flange Off Output Shaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
